|MKOThe ability of a thief to use his or her cunning and quickness to
outsmart an opponent has always been of utmost advantage in battle.
Once a thief reaches the 12th guild level, they are able to circle
quickly around an opponent and deliver a well placed slash in the
opponent's back. This skill takes time for a thief to recover from
but as the thief progresses in level, quickness, and within the
guild, they will see the time it takes to recover from this maneuver
lessen. A thief may also see increased precision on a strike 
when an opponent is temporarily blinded.

|CKOGLVL required: |GKB12
